## PatternFly Design System (MANDATORY)

> **CRITICAL:** This project MUST use PatternFly Design System exclusively. No exceptions.

### ABSOLUTE RULES:

1. **NEVER use inline styles** (`style={{...}}`) - Use PatternFly component props
2. **NEVER create custom CSS classes** - Use PatternFly layout components
3. **NEVER write custom CSS** - index.css should be minimal or empty
4. **ALWAYS use PatternFly spacing props** - `spaceItems`, `gap`, `hasGutter`
5. **ALWAYS use PatternFly layout components** - Flex, Stack, Split, Grid

### PatternFly Component Mapping:

| Need | PatternFly Solution |
|------|---------------------|
| Spacing between elements | `hasGutter` prop on Stack/Split/Flex |
| Margins | `spacer` prop on FlexItem, or use Stack/Split |
| Horizontal layout | `<Split hasGutter>` or `<Flex>` |
| Vertical layout | `<Stack hasGutter>` or `<Flex direction="column">` |
| Colors | PatternFly `Label color` prop, `Alert variant` |
| Typography | `<Content component="p/h1/h2/small">` |
| Centering | `<Flex alignItems="center" justifyContent="center">` |
| App layout | `<Page>`, `<PageSidebar>`, `<PageSection>` |
| Side panels | `<Drawer position="bottom/start/end">` |
| Card spacing | `<CardBody>` has built-in padding |
| Form spacing | `<Form>`, `<FormGroup>` have built-in spacing |

### Common Transformations:

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG - Inline styles
<div style={{ marginTop: '16px', display: 'flex', gap: '8px' }}>

// ✅ CORRECT - PatternFly
<Flex spaceItems={{ default: 'spaceItemsSm' }}>
```

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG - Custom margins
<Alert style={{ marginBottom: 16 }}>

// ✅ CORRECT - Stack with gutter
<Stack hasGutter>
  <StackItem><Alert>...</Alert></StackItem>
  <StackItem>Next content</StackItem>
</Stack>
```

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG - Custom layout CSS
<div className="my-sidebar">

// ✅ CORRECT - PatternFly Page
<Page sidebar={<PageSidebar>...</PageSidebar>}>
```

### Spacing Props Reference:

- **hasGutter** - Adds default gap between children
- **spaceItems** - `none`, `xs`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`, `2xl`, `3xl`, `4xl`
- **gap** / `rowGap` / `columnGap` - CSS gap with same size values
- **padding** - Object with breakpoint keys: `{ default: 'noPadding', md: 'padding' }`

### Layout Components:

| Component | Use Case |
|-----------|----------|
| `Page` | Main app shell |
| `PageSidebar` | Left navigation |
| `PageSection` | Content sections with padding |
| `Drawer` | Slide-out panels (bottom for logs/terminal) |
| `Stack` | Vertical layout |
| `Split` | Horizontal layout |
| `Flex` | Complex flexbox layouts |
| `Grid` | CSS Grid layouts |

### Official References:

- **Layouts:** https://www.patternfly.org/layouts/flex
- **Spacing:** https://www.patternfly.org/design-foundations/spacers
- **Page:** https://www.patternfly.org/components/page
- **Drawer:** https://www.patternfly.org/components/drawer
- **All Components:** https://www.patternfly.org/components/all-components

### Enforcement:

Before committing any component:
1. `grep -r "style={{" src/` should return ZERO results
2. `grep -r "className=\"[^pf]" src/` should return ZERO custom classes
3. All spacing should use PatternFly props, not CSS

